1 a. the amount of the expenditure,
2 b. the date the expenditure was paid,
3 c. the name of the individual or entity to which the
4 expenditure was paid,
5 d. if the expenditure is a payment to an employee, the
6 employee's job title or other information that
7 identifies their role within the organization, and
8 e. each transaction from a state agency shall be assigned
9 an expenditure category defined by the U.S. Census
10 Bureau;
11 2. The ability to search or browse all individual expenditures
12 in each fiscal year;
13 3. The ability to aggregate data and where appropriate, through
14 interactive software, generate totals, averages, and other summary
15 statistics broken down by year, Submitting Party, spending
16 categories described in paragraph 1 of this section and other
17 criteria that may be useful to the public;
18 4. The ability to easily download all or a subset of
19 expenditure data in a format that is widely usable and useful to
20 members of the public; and
21 5. The ability to browse and search anonymized annual salary
22 and benefit information for all employees of the Submitting Party.
